    "Page SixB Quaker City Dorcas Class Plans To Hold Bazaar And Supper At Garfield Hall Nov 7 A meeting of the Dorcas class of the Christian church was held recently at the parsonage De votions were led by Mrs Eleanor Hughes The business session was conducted by Sarah King presi dent Games and contests were con ducted by Mrs Hazel McBurney Hostesses were Mrs Luella Gar dner and Mrs Ruth Brown Mrs Leslie Morgan was received as a new member Personals Mrs Ethel Johnson and Mrs Leslie Fowler of Barnesville route visited the gardens of Zoar and Schoenbrunn recently Also on the trip they viewed one of the two remaining old his torical block houses located near Isleta Mrs Charles Stevens spent a part of last week with her daugh ter Mrs Roger Scott and family Of Salesville route Howard Forsythe Columbus barber son of Mr and Mrs E C Forsythe and three other com panions from that city have re turned from a vacation and deer and antelope hunting expedition near Douglas Wyoming They made the trip by station wagon and were gone two weeks Mr and Mrs Wilbur Moore re cently visited Mr and Mrs Fred Moss of"
